      <body>

         <fw type="continued" place="right"><date>November 25, 1929.</date></fw>
         <fw type="continued" place="left">To:&#160;<name ref="pers:CGS1">Mr. C. Gardner
               Sullivan</name></fw>
         <fw type="continued" place="right">From:&#160;<name ref="pers:WE1">Mrs. Reeve</name></fw>
         <fw type="continued" place="center">RE:&#160;<emph>CREDIT</emph></fw>

         <div type="content">



            <p>I am going to ask that I be given credit for the original story as well as the
               dialogue of <q>BARBARY COAST</q>. <name ref="pers:CL2">Charley Logue</name> should
               share credit with me for the story inasmuch as although I wrote the story he
               contributed much by his suggestions in the plotting.</p>
         </div>

         <div type="content">

            <fw type="continued" place="center">RE:&#160;<emph>CARNIVAL</emph></fw>

            <p>May I also be given the full credit for the screen story and dialogue, I wrote this
               in its entirety - a detailed script with dialogue of eighty-six pages practically
               ready to broken up.</p>

         </div>
      </body>
